## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent data and the inherent biases in opinion-based sources. Additionally, the effectiveness of standardized testing can vary significantly depending on the context, such as the specific educational environment and the demographic characteristics of the student population. Further empirical research is needed to draw more definitive conclusions.

